This gas stove protector can withstand temperatures up to 500 degrees Fahrenheit. Essential Kitchen Gadget: These gas hob protectors are the solution to your messy cooking ways. Lay flat on your stove and make your stove look neat and clean so you can cook without worry. With this gas stove protectors you can now cook without the worry of needing to scrape or scrub.

Easy to resize: No need to worry about the different sizes of the stove, this gas stove top covers can be cut with scissors, it can adapt to most stoves of different sizes. Just remove your gas grate, mark it over your protector sheet, fold the stove covers then cut.

Easy To Clean & Dishwasher Safe: Easy to wipe off the dripping sauce, charred food, grease. Do not throw it away when the surface is dirty. It is fully reusable on both sides, and also can be easily removed and washed by hot soapy water! Or just throw the dirty stove protector liners in the dishwasher and it will be a new one again.

Package Included: There are 8 Pcs Gas Stove Covers + 2 Pcs Silicone Stove Gap Covers(black) in the package, so you can replace them as needed. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I always used foil on my stove but I found this stove covers. Works perfect, keeps my stove clean, and reusable. Wish I found this along time ago!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not perfect but pretty good
reviews.reviewText: I've used these for 2 years on my gas stove. They're easy enough to clean--just brush off any food on them and toss them in the washing machine. They do keep most of the messes contained and manageable. They're not foolproof, though. If something bubbles over on the stove, the liquid will definitely get underneath these covers and make a mess. They're also not entirely flame resistant. I have different sized burners on my stove, and sometimes the one specifically trimmed for each burner doesn't make it back to the right spot. After 2 years of use, most of them have burned edges and have become too brittle to use anymore. (And I've been concerned about what fumes that burning silicone must have put into the air in my house.) All in all, they work pretty well even though they're not a perfect solution. I'm considering buying another set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 26, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I use these burner covers on my gas stove. I have one of those “fancy” stoves with the big iron grates and power burner gas jets. These burners put out a big flame. I got tired to trying to scrub the burned on food, so I gave these a try. Well, they are just perfect. The heat and fire from the jet doesn’t seem to affect these. I don’t know what they’re made of, but it sure is capable of handing a lot of heat. When I clean the stove I shake these off and wash the crumbs and stuff down the garbage disposal. Then I fill the sink with warm water and a squirt of dish soap. Soak them for a few mins and rinse and you’re good to go again. On thing to note is that some food will burn to these mat covers. You’ll end up with a cover that has some burned on food—like charcoal. However, I’d much rather have it burn on the cover than on the stove and have to scrub it off. I definitely recommend these.
